<help>
    <tab id="MENU_0">
        <page id="PANEL_0">
            <page_title class="H2">Student Enrollment</page_title>
            <section>
                <title class="H3">Overview</title>
                <text>
                    The Report Manager loads a list of student information that is exported from MyEd in a 'comma separated values' (CSV) file. Student data in this file is
                    organized by grade and gender and is used to ensure that report card comments utilize each student's correct name and gender.
                </text>
            </section>
            <section>
                <title class="H3">Loading Data From MyEd</title>
                <image name="T0P0 student enrollment.png" path="T0P0"/>
                <text>
                    The CSV file needs to contain specific data fields that can be selected from MyEd when creating a 'Quick Report'. The link below provides a visual
                    tutorial on exporting student data from MyEd.
                </text>
                <link url="https://github.com/Peace-Robotics-Studio/report-manager/wiki/Obtaining-Data-From-MyEd" alt="Report Manager Wiki">Instructions for exporting student data from MyEd</link>
            </section>
            <section>
                <title class="H3">Choose CSV File</title>
                <image name="T0P0 select csv file.png" path="T0P0"/>
                <text>
                    Choose a CSV file to load by clicking on the picture of the folder.
                </text>
            </section>
            <section>
                <title class="H3">Remember CSV File Location</title>
                <image name="T0P0 save path.png" path="T0P0"/>
                <text>
                    Select this option (default) to allow the Report Manager to remember the last CSV file you used.
                </text>
            </section>
        </page>
        <page id="PANEL_1">
            <page_title class="H2">Gender Pronouns</page_title>
            <section>
                <title class="H3">Overview</title>
                <text>
                    Student gender identities can be set in this panel. The default gender pronouns used when checking a comment are based on the student's registered gender. If MyEd lists a gender identity, then
                    this value is used instead. Additional genders and pronouns can be defined in this panel.
                </text>
            </section>
        </page>
    </tab>
